[[cdo:9 nguŏk 12 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:9 goe̍h 12 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:九月十二]] {{Lunisolar September}} '''September 12''' is the 12th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Bun'ei|ja|文永}} 8th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1271]] [[October 17]]） – {{ill|Nichiren|ja|日蓮}} was exiled to {{ill|Sado Island|ja|佐渡島}}. * {{ill|Genki|ja|元亨}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1570]] [[October 11]]） – The 【本願寺 Kōsa】 of the Hongan-ji called on adherents in various provinces to rise up and attack {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長}}, thus beginning the decade-long 【Ishiyama War】. * {{ill|Genki|ja|元亨}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1571]] [[September 30]]） – {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長}} carried out the 【Mount Hiei Arson Incident】. * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1872]] [[October 14]]） – Japan's first formal railway, running between 【Shinbashi】 and 【Yokohama】, was officially opened; service began the following day (【Railway Day】).
== Births ==
== Deaths == * {{ill|Taika|ja|大化|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[645]] [[October 7]]） – {{ill|Kobun Daikō Ōkimi|ja|古人大兄皇子}}, the first son of {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇}} (birth year unknown). * {{ill|Chian (era)|ja|治安}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1022]] [[October 10]]） – {{ill|Tōshi Naishinnō|ja|当子内親王}}, the first princess of {{ill|Emperor Sanjō|ja|三条天皇}} (born [[1001]]). * {{ill|Ninji|ja|人治}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1242]] [[October 7]]） – {{ill|Shuntoku Tennō|ja|順徳天皇}}, the 84th Emperor of Japan (born [[1197]]). * {{ill|Genna|ja|元和}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1619]] [[October 19]]） – {{ill|Fujiwara Sokaka|ja|藤原惺窩}}, a Confucian scholar (儒学者/儒生) (born [[1561]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1631]] [[October 7]]） – {{ill|Katō Yoshiaki|ja|加藤嘉明}}, lord of the {{ill|Iyo Matsuyama Domain|ja|伊予松山藩}} (born [[1563]]). * {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1664]] [[October 30]]） – {{ill|Nambu Shigenao|ja|南部重直}}, the 2nd lord of the {{ill|Morioka Domain|ja|盛岡藩}} (born [[1606]]). * {{ill|Shōtoku (era)|ja|正徳}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1711]] [[October 23]]） – {{ill|Matsudaira Masachika|ja|松平昌親}}, lord of the {{ill|Fukui Domain|ja|福井藩}} (born [[1640]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1821]] [[October 7]]） – {{ill|Hanawa Hokiichi|ja|塙保己一}}, a scholar of national literature (国文学者) (born [[1746]]).
