{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月十二|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 12일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 12''' is the 12th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Bun'ei|Bun'ei]] 8th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1271]] [[October 17]]） – [[:en:Nichiren|Nichiren]] was exiled to [[:en:Sado Island|Sado Island]]. * [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genki]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1570]] [[October 11]]） – The 【本願寺 Kōsa】 of the Hongan-ji called on adherents in various provinces to rise up and attack [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]], thus beginning the decade-long 【Ishiyama War】. * [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genki]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1571]] [[September 30]]） – [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]] carried out the 【Mount Hiei Arson Incident】. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[October 14]]） – Japan's first formal railway, running between 【Shinbashi】 and 【Yokohama】, was officially opened; service began the following day (【Railway Day】).
